◆ anglemod()

float anglemod ( float  a)

Converts an angle to a value between 0 and 360 degrees.

This function ensures an angle stays within a full circle (0-360 degrees). For example, if an angle is 370 degrees, it will be converted to 10 degrees.

Parameters
aThe angle to normalize
Returns
The normalized angle between 0 and 360 degrees
